{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01AySRH6CzJF4PWL6767Jtvj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Elections are now stable.\n\n**What was wrong:** The replica set `rs0` had only two data-bearing members (both voting). An even number of voters can't reliably break ties, so elections were unstable. A `mongo-arb-0` arbiter pod was running but was **not** a member of the replica set config.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Added `mongo-arb-0.mongo-arb.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017` to the replica set as an **arbiter** (`rs.addArb`). An arbiter votes but stores no data → odd vote count (3), no added storage cost, and no new data-bearing member.\n2. The first attempt was rejected because moving from a 2-member set to a Primary-Secondary-Arbiter topology changes the implicit default write concern. I set an explicit cluster default (`setDefaultRWConcern` → `w:\"majority\"`) and the reconfig succeeded.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- Members: `mongo-rs-0` PRIMARY, `mongo-rs-1` SECONDARY, `mongo-arb-0` ARBITER — all `health=1`, 3 votes total.\n- App data intact: `app.test` still has 3 documents."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":568,"cache_read_input_tokens":36704,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":568},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8324e79-4e6a-4757-b2da-995f95be2227","uuid":"97664dc6-5d01-4856-9f92-7e555289c231","request_id":"req_011CcAi4v4U9jiF4rjbFopAd"}
